      <body>
        <div>
            <pb facs="#TL-0414.jpg" n="part3_p022.jpg" xml:id="img_0022" corresp="https://id.acdh.oeaw.ac.at/tillich-lectures/part3_p022.jpg"/>
            
            <p facs="#facs_22_tr_1">
               <lb facs="#facs_22_tr_1_tl_1" n="N001"/>pour lui
               <lb facs="#facs_22_tr_1_tl_2" n="N002"/>409.
               <lb facs="#facs_22_tr_1_tl_3" n="N003"/> : uevelopment of one’s unique individual potentialities, in the process of one's life. This is the
               <lb facs="#facs_22_tr_1_tl_4" n="N004"/>second reason for the humanistic ideal of' education.
               <lb facs="#facs_22_tr_1_tl_5" n="N005"/>Then there is a third one: man, because of his central position in the universe, is able to
               <lb facs="#facs_22_tr_1_tl_6" n="N006"/>decide automously, by the law of the structure of mind and universe which is [bodied] in him,
               <lb facs="#facs_22_tr_1_tl_7" n="N007"/>controls world and
               <lb facs="#facs_22_tr_1_tl_8" n="N008"/>about the true and the good. Man in the power of his automomous reason
               <lb facs="#facs_22_tr_1_tl_9" n="N009"/>nature and society. "Autonomous" means: the law is in himself. Please don’t misunderstand that
               <lb facs="#facs_22_tr_1_tl_10" n="N010"/>word—I must say that now for 50 years, each time, because of the Istortion the concept of
               <lb facs="#facs_22_tr_1_tl_11" n="N011"/>autonomy has suffered in Neo-Orthodor theology, where it has been identified with individual
               <lb facs="#facs_22_tr_1_tl_12" n="N012"/>subjection
               <lb facs="#facs_22_tr_1_tl_13" n="N013"/>to the law of the
               <lb facs="#facs_22_tr_1_tl_14" n="N014"/>willfuiness. "Autonomous" is, as the Greek word nomos indicates,
               <lb facs="#facs_22_tr_1_tl_15" n="N015"/>universe which is embodied in man and reality as a whole. Autonomy in Kant is just the opposite
               <lb facs="#facs_22_tr_1_tl_16" n="N016"/>of willfulness: Kant construes willfulness as heteronomy, as dependent on one's whims, desires,ioars,
            </p>
            <p facs="#facs_22_tr_2">
               <lb facs="#facs_22_tr_2_tl_1" n="N001"/>anxiety, etc. That’sPeteronomy, and that's used by ecclesiastical and political authorities in order
               <lb facs="#facs_22_tr_2_tl_2" n="N002"/>to impose STRANGE laws, HETERONOMOUS laws, upon people. nothing of this is implied
               <lb facs="#facs_22_tr_2_tl_3" n="N003"/>in the concept of autonomy.
               <lb facs="#facs_22_tr_2_tl_4" n="N004"/>So we have these three ideas: 1) Man can recognize the law of the universe in himself and
               <lb facs="#facs_22_tr_2_tl_5" n="N005"/>in his world. 2) Man is a unique individual, actualizing unique potentialities, irrepeatably.
               <lb facs="#facs_22_tr_2_tl_6" n="N006"/>3) And man is the microcosm in whom all the levels and dimensions of reality are united.
               <lb facs="#facs_22_tr_2_tl_7" n="N007"/>This immediately gives to the problem of education a definite content: make actual
               <lb facs="#facs_22_tr_2_tl_8" n="N008"/>4
               <lb facs="#facs_22_tr_2_tl_9" n="N009"/>what is potential in man; help him to come to autonomy; help¬ him to Jevelop his individual
               <lb facs="#facs_22_tr_2_tl_10" n="N010"/>Ama
               <lb facs="#facs_22_tr_2_tl_11" n="N011"/>der
               <lb facs="#facs_22_tr_2_tl_12" n="N012"/>potentalities; help him to mirror the universe in his mind.
               <lb facs="#facs_22_tr_2_tl_13" n="N013"/>In the period in which it was first conceived, this humanistic idea of course demanded,
               <lb facs="#facs_22_tr_2_tl_14" n="N014"/>Säjéling
               <lb facs="#facs_22_tr_2_tl_15" n="N015"/>and partly carried through, a very special form of education-the private, aristocratic education,
               <lb facs="#facs_22_tr_2_tl_16" n="N016"/>as niusseau in his Emile (and others) demanded, an education in which the educator concentrates
            </p>
            <p facs="#facs_22_tr_3">
               <lb facs="#facs_22_tr_3_tl_1" n="N001"/>dʼune manière beaucoup
               <lb facs="#facs_22_tr_3_tl_2" n="N002"/>Cela nʼentraîne pour entretien
               <lb facs="#facs_22_tr_3_tl_3" n="N003"/>dʼune manière
               <lb facs="#facs_22_tr_3_tl_4" n="N004"/>Monsieur,
               <lb facs="#facs_22_tr_3_tl_5" n="N005"/>Monsieur,
               <lb facs="#facs_22_tr_3_tl_6" n="N006"/>dʼun autre
               <lb facs="#facs_22_tr_3_tl_7" n="N007"/>G.C.F.P
               <lb facs="#facs_22_tr_3_tl_8" n="N008"/>de mon frere,
               <lb facs="#facs_22_tr_3_tl_9" n="N009"/>Monsieur
               <lb facs="#facs_22_tr_3_tl_10" n="N010"/>dʼun autre
               <lb facs="#facs_22_tr_3_tl_11" n="N011"/>dʼacquerir que je suis
               <lb facs="#facs_22_tr_3_tl_12" n="N012"/>dʼadresse à
            </p>
            
